  "prompt": "What are some tips on making it through the job interview process at Park National?",
  "response": "I can offer some general interview tips that could be helpful for interviewing at Park National:\n\n1. Research the company thoroughly\n- Learn about Park National's history, values, and current business operations\n- Understand their banking services and community focus\n\n2. Prepare for common banking interview questions\n- Be ready to discuss your customer service experience\n- Highlight your attention to detail and financial knowledge\n- Demonstrate your understanding of banking regulations\n\n3. Professional presentation\n- Dress professionally and conservatively\n- Arrive 10-15 minutes early\n- Bring extra copies of your resume\n- Show a positive, confident attitude\n\n4. Practice common interview questions\n- Tell me about yourself\n- Why do you want to work at Park National?\n- What are your strengths and weaknesses?\n\n5. Showcase relevant skills\n- Communication skills\n- Problem-solving abilities\n- Teamwork\n- Customer service orientation\n\n6. Follow up after the interview\n- Send a thank you email within 24-48 hours\n- Reiterate your interest in the position\n\nWhile these are general tips, they should help you prepare for an interview at Park National. The specific details might vary depending on the exact role you're applying for.",
